";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=144050\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:452:\"<p>Would you like to know how to get featured snippets on Google? The featured snippet is a much-coveted search engine results page (SERP) feature that can help you boost your organic clickthrough rates (CTRs) and drive traffic to your site.&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-get-featured-snippets-on-google/\">How to Get Featured Snippets on Google [A Beginners Guide]</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19098:\"<p>Would you like to know how to get featured snippets on Google?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The featured snippet is a much-coveted <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-are-serps/\" title=\"What Are SERPs (And Why Are they Important to SEO)?\">search engine results page</a> (SERP) feature that can help you boost your organic clickthrough rates (CTRs) and drive traffic to your site. Therefore, featured snippets are invaluable assets that can help boost business growth.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, weâ€™ll show you how to get featured snippets on Google, even if youâ€™re not a WordPress expert.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-a-google-featured-snippet\">What is a Google Featured Snippet?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-are-google-featured-snippets-important-to-seo\">Why are Google Featured Snippets Important to SEO?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-greater-visibility-for-your-content\">Greater Visibility for Your Content</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-improve-your-organic-ctrs-and-boost-your-traffic\">Improve Your Organic CTRs and Boost Your Traffic</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-get-featured-snippets-on-google\">How to Get Featured Snippets on Google</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-1-install-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">1. Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-2-implement-schema-markup\">2. Implement Schema Markup</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-3-optimize-content-structure-for-featured-snippets\">3. Optimize Content Structure for Featured Snippets</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-4-use-a-table-of-contents\">4. Use a Table of Contents</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-5-create-the-best-piece-of-content-on-the-subject\">5. Create the Best Piece of Content on the Subject</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-6-check-out-your-competitors\">6. Check Out Your Competitors</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-now-you-know-how-to-get-featured-snippets-on-google\">Now You Know How to Get Featured Snippets on Google</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-a-google-featured-snippet\">What is a Google Featured Snippet?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A featured snippet, also called position zero, is the search listing that appears after ads and sponsored posts (depending on current SERP features) but above the first organic result. They are designed to give users a quick answer to their search query by providing more information than traditional search snippets.Â </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-1.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to get featured snippets lands you the top spot on SERPs.\" class=\"wp-image-153407\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-1-300x228.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-1-600x456.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An important point to note is that search engines pull information from websites to generate featured snippets. This is why you should know the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\" title=\"A Complete Blog Post SEO Checklist to Boost Rankings\">SEO best practices</a> that give you better chances of getting featured snippets on Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And thatâ€™s exactly what weâ€™ll show you in a moment.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Itâ€™s up to Googleâ€™s discretion whether you land the featured snippet or not. The tips presented in this article are a guide to help optimize for the featured snippet and are not a guarantee youâ€™ll get it.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-are-google-featured-snippets-important-to-seo\">Why are Google Featured Snippets Important to SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Getting featured snippets is crucial to your SEO for several reasons, the main ones being:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-greater-visibility-for-your-content\">Greater Visibility for Your Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>By virtue of their position and size, featured snippets are very prominent SERP features that canâ€™t be missed. They are prime real estate on SERPs that can help boost your brand awareness.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-improve-your-organic-ctrs-and-boost-your-traffic\">Improve Your Organic CTRs and Boost Your Traffic</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another advantage of getting the featured snippet for your keyword is that it leads to improved organic CTRs. Research shows that featured snippets get about <a href=\"https://www.searchenginewatch.com/2020/12/03/research-insights-role-of-featured-snippets-in-website-traffic-boost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">35.1% of clicks</a> on the first page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thanks to this improvement in CTRs, you also get a boost in traffic to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Getting the featured snippet, as you can see, is critical to business growth.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-get-featured-snippets-on-google\">How to Get Featured Snippets on Google</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to optimize your content for featured snippets?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Letâ€™s dive right in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-1-install-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">1. Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to optimizing your content for featured snippets is to install a powerful SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo.png\" alt=\"aioseo homepae\" class=\"wp-image-151544\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is the best WordPress SEO plugin on the market and is trusted by over 3 million savvy website owners and marketers to help them dominate the SERPs and drive relevant traffic to their sites. This is because the plugin has many <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\" title=\"Features\">powerful SEO features and modules</a> to help you optimize your website for search engines and users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the plugin&#8217;s most popular features are designed to help you rank your content easily and get the featured snippet. These are features like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Next-gen Schema Generator</li><li>FAQ and table of contents blocks</li><li>SEO Analysis module</li><li>TrueSEO on-page analysis tool</li><li>And more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on how to install AIOSEO, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-2-implement-schema-markup\">2. Implement Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Schema markup, also called structured data, helps search engines better understand your content and its context. As a result, they can generate better search snippets.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More importantly, schema markup helps you get the featured snippet. This is especially if you use the following schema types:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>FAQ schema</li><li>How-to schema</li><li>Recipe schema</li><li>Product schema</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding these schema types is super easy with AIOSEOâ€™s next-gen Schema Generator, even if you have no technical or coding knowledge.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, open your target page or post in editor mode and scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO Settings</strong> section. Next, click <strong>Schema Â» Generate Schema</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"420\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/product-rich-snippets-adding-schema-01.png\" alt=\"Generating schema markup is easy with AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-133537\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/product-rich-snippets-adding-schema-01.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/product-rich-snippets-adding-schema-01-300x180.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/product-rich-snippets-adding-schema-01-600x360.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking the <strong>Generate Schema</strong> button will open our <strong>Schema Catalog,</strong> from which you can choose the schema you want to implement.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"472\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/schema-generator-catalog.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO\'s Schema Catalog helps you add any type of schema markup in WordPress.\" class=\"wp-image-120239\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/schema-generator-catalog.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/schema-generator-catalog-300x202.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/schema-generator-catalog-600x405.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on how to add schema markup in WordPress, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin/\" title=\"How to Add Schema Markup to WordPress Without a Plugin\">check out this detailed guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-3-optimize-content-structure-for-featured-snippets\">3. Optimize Content Structure for Featured Snippets</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to increase your chances of getting the featured snippet is to optimize your content for the featured snippet. Doing so includes simple elements like using question-based heading tags immediately followed by an answer containing the keyword in the question.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"425\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-QA.png\" alt=\"Heading tags are a great way to optimize your content for featured snippets.\" class=\"wp-image-153412\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-QA.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-QA-300x182.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-QA-600x363.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Structuring your content this way gives search engines fantastic passages to pull into the featured snippet box.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Other ways to optimize your content for search snippets include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Using short paragraphs to provide direct answers to searchers&#8217; questions</li><li>Breaking down tutorials into steps and labeling them as such</li><li>Compressing large amounts of data into tables</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Most featured snippets contain short, succinct, and concise answers to questions. Therefore, optimizing content structure makes it easier for search engines to pull information from your site when generating a featured snippet.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-4-use-a-table-of-contents\">4. Use a Table of Contents</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to optimize your content for featured snippets is to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)\">add a table of contents to your posts</a>. This is because a table of contents provides search engines with bullet points they can easily pull from to present in a list-style featured snippet.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"477\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-3.png\" alt=\"Adding a table of contents helps you generate a list-style featured snippet.\" class=\"wp-image-153413\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-3.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-3-300x204.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-3-600x408.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding a table of contents manually in WordPress can be laborious and time-consuming. But with AIOSEO, itâ€™s simply a matter of adding our Table of Contents block where you want to place your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do so, simply add a block as you normally would and select the <strong>AIOSEO Table of Contents</strong> block option:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"498\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-1.png\" alt=\"Adding a table of contents is super easy with AIOSEO.\" class=\"wp-image-153414\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-1-300x213.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-1-600x427.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you add the Table of Contents block, AIOSEO will automatically create your table of contents from your heading tags. Plus, the table of contents will be hyperlinked so users can jump to the section they want right from the table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most importantly, regarding SEO, the table of contents also helps you stand a better chance of landing the featured snippet for your keyword.Â </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-5-create-the-best-piece-of-content-on-the-subject\">5. Create the Best Piece of Content on the Subject</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engines want to show users the best possible results for a search query. This is why you just invest time and resources to ensure you create the best possible piece of content on your subject. This is a piece of content that addresses all the questions searchers may have. It also means creating an article that follows SEO best practices to help it rank better. Examples include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-link-assistant-to-optimize-your-internal-linking-strategy/\" title=\"How to Use Link Assistant to Optimize Your Internal Linking Strategy\">Adding internal links</a> for topical authority</li><li>Craft <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-check-if-your-google-search-snippets-are-properly-optimized/\" title=\"How to Check If Your Google Search Snippets Are Properly Optimized\">optimized Google search snippets</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-improve-readability-score-on-wordpress-step-by-step/\">Optimize for readability</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>For more tips, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\" title=\"SEO Best Practices: 20 Ultimate SEO Tips to Boost Rankings\">guide to SEO best practices</a>.Â </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-6-check-out-your-competitors\">6. Check Out Your Competitors</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Conducting a competitor analysis is another excellent way to help you determine how to land the featured snippet. An easy way to do this is to use a tool like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Ahrefs\">Ahrefs</a>. Simply go to <strong>Site Explorer (enter competitors domain) Â» Organic keywords Â» SERP Features Â» Featured snippets</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"388\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-ahrefs-3.png\" alt=\"Ahrefs can help you check the organic keywords your competitors have the featured snippet for.\" class=\"wp-image-153415\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-ahrefs-3.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-ahrefs-3-300x166.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-get-featured-snippets-ahrefs-3-600x333.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Doing so will show you all the keywords your competitor has the featured snippet for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, use AIOSEOâ€™s SEO Analysis tool to analyze your competitorâ€™s SEO to see what theyâ€™re doing to enhance their chances of landing featured snippets.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"331\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/what-are-serps-competitor-analysis.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO\'s competitor analysis feature helps you better analyze your competitors SEO.\" class=\"wp-image-151546\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/what-are-serps-competitor-analysis.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/what-are-serps-competitor-analysis-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/what-are-serps-competitor-analysis-600x283.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on conducting a competitor analysis in WordPress, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\" title=\"How to Do an SEO Competitor Analysis [The Easy Way]\">check out this detailed guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Competitor analysis will give you insight into what works for your competitors and help you replicate their winning SEO strategies.Â </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-now-you-know-how-to-get-featured-snippets-on-google\">Now You Know How to Get Featured Snippets on Google</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you learn how to get featured snippets on Google. You may also want to check out other articles on our blog, like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/\" title=\"How to Properly Set Up SEO for Different Languages and Countries\">how to set up SEO for different languages</a> and our tutorial on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-orphan-pages-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Easily Find and Fix Orphan Pages in WordPress\">how to easily find and fix orphan pages in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. Youâ€™ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-get-featured-snippets-on-google/\">How to Get Featured Snippets on Google [A Beginners Guide]</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-get-featured-snippets-on-google/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"â€‹â€‹What is Google Knowledge Graph? A Super Simple Explanation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:124:\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-knowledge-graph/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=what-is-google-knowledge-graph\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-knowledge-graph/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 19 Jan 2023 14:11:48 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"google knowledge graph\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"knowledge panels\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"what is google knowledge graph\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=152247\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:438:\"<p>Are you looking for a simple explanation of what Google Knowledge Graph is? You may be wondering if it&#8217;s related to SEO or if you need to take action on it. In this article, we&#8217;ll explain the Google Knowledge Graph&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-knowledge-graph/\">â€‹â€‹What is Google Knowledge Graph? A Super Simple Explanation</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16609:\"<p>Are you looking for a simple explanation of what Google Knowledge Graph is?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may be wondering if it&#8217;s related to SEO or if you need to take action on it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll explain the Google Knowledge Graph in plain everyday language and why it&#8217;s so interesting.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-google-knowledge-graph\">What is Google Knowledge Graph?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-a-giant-drive-through-warehouse\">Billions of Items</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-where-does-google-knowledge-graph-get-its-data-from\">Where Does Google Knowledge Graph Get Its Data From?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-are-zero-click-results\">What Are Zero-Click Results?</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-seo-should-i-change-anything-for-google-knowledge-graph\">SEO: Should I Change Anything for Google Knowledge Graph?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-add-schema-easily-with-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Add Schema Easily With All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a><ul></ul></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-whats-next\">What&#8217;s Next?</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-google-knowledge-graph\">What is Google Knowledge Graph?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Google&#8217;s Knowledge Graph is a database containing billions of facts about people and things and the relationships between them. It also learns from past searcher behavior to understand what other searchers may want.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The goal of the Knowledge Graph is to display publicly known facts in response to Google searches for people, places, or things.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example of how these facts may appear. We did a search for musician Esperanza Spalding and got this engaging grid of images, videos, and buttons:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"391\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-graph-1024x391.jpg\" alt=\"google knowledge graph esperanza spalding\" class=\"wp-image-152256\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-graph-1024x391.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-graph-300x115.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-graph-768x293.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-graph-600x229.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-graph-157x60.jpg 157w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-graph-236x90.jpg 236w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-graph.jpg 1387w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the right side of the page, we get more information about Esperanza and her music, including various ways to listen:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"512\" height=\"657\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-panel-2.png\" alt=\"google knowledge graph example\" class=\"wp-image-152258\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-panel-2.png 512w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-panel-2-234x300.png 234w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-panel-2-47x60.png 47w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/esperanza-spalding-knowledge-panel-2-70x90.png 70w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The 1st display is creative and enticing while the 2nd one is more like an encyclopedia summary. Both are &#8216;fed&#8217; by Knowledge Graph.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And both displays are called <strong>Knowledge Panels</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-a-giant-drive-through-warehouse\">A Giant Drive-Through Warehouse</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can think of Knowledge Graph as a giant drive-through warehouse. You pull up and say what you&#8217;re looking for. (&#8220;I want a big juicy cheeseburger.&#8221;) Then robots race to fetch what you asked for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you go through the drive-through at McDonald&#8217;s, you order from the menu: &#8220;I want a Big Mac.&#8221; You might add details: &#8220;I want a Big Mac, with cheese and bacon. Hold the pickle.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But when people ask for things in Google Search, there aren&#8217;t any menus. So people describe what they want in lots of different ways.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>I want the biggest burger you got!</li><li>I want a hot, juicy burger that fills me up!</li><li>I want a delicious hot meal. What do you suggest?</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowledge Graph has helped Google get very good at understanding what people want when they ask for things, <em>regardless of the ways they ask for them.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google uses something called natural language processing (<a href=\"https://research.google/research-areas/natural-language-processing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">NLP</a>) to do this.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And everything the Knowledge Graph delivers comes in response to search queries.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-whats-a-search-query\">What&#8217;s a search query?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A search query is a request made to a search engine, either by typing or <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-add-voice-search-to-your-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">speaking</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>At a fast-food drive-through, your request is called an &#8220;order.&#8221;</li><li>When you&#8217;re using a search engine, your request is called a &#8220;search term&#8221; or &#8220;search query.&#8221;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-where-does-google-knowledge-graph-get-its-data-from\">Where Does Google Knowledge Graph Get Its Data From?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When Google initially announced the Knowledge Graph they cited some of their information sources:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Wikipedia</li><li>Freebase</li><li>CIA World FactBook.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>(In 2014 Freebase migrated its data to Wikidata.org.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, Google licenses and pulls data from various industry sources, including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Weather.com</li><li>Morningstar</li><li>Refinitiv</li><li>ICE Data Services (Intercontinental Commodity Exchange)</li><li>NYSE (New York Stock Exchange)</li><li>Coinmarketcap</li><li>S&amp;P Capital IQ</li><li>TickerPlant</li><li>S&amp;P Dow Jones Indices.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>(Note: Asset prices displayed in search results are not always &#8220;real-time&#8221; data. They may be delayed by 5-15 minutes or more. You can learn more from Google&#8217;s <a href=\"https://www.google.com/intl/en_us/googlefinance/disclaimer/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">disclaimer</a>.)</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-are-zero-click-results\">What Are Zero-Click Results?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Google&#8217;s Knowledge Graph has contributed to a phenomenon called &#8220;zero-click results.&#8221; This refers to getting an answer to your search query <em>without having to click on a website</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, a search for &#8220;current NFL scoreâ€ returned this result, which has the score of the Miami Dolphins &#8211; Buffalo Bills game which, at the time, was in &#8220;Q3&#8221; (the 3rd quarter).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"510\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-nfl-score-example-1024x510.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152260\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-nfl-score-example-1024x510.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-nfl-score-example-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-nfl-score-example-768x382.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-nfl-score-example-600x299.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-nfl-score-example-121x60.png 121w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-nfl-score-example-181x90.png 181w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-nfl-score-example.png 1139w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s another example: a search for the stock symbol &#8220;CEF&#8221; and &#8220;price&#8221; returns this.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"630\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-stock-price-example-1024x630.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152262\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-stock-price-example-1024x630.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-stock-price-example-300x185.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-stock-price-example-768x473.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-stock-price-example-600x369.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-stock-price-example-97x60.png 97w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-stock-price-example-146x90.png 146w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/zero-click-stock-price-example.png 1254w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-should-i-be-concerned-about-zero-click-results\">Should I be Concerned About Zero-Click Results?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Zero-click results are an evolution of Google&#8217;s quest to better serve searchers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Suppose you&#8217;re using things like live sports scores and stock prices or encyclopedia-style facts to attract site visitors. In that case, you should look carefully at Google&#8217;s zero-click results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then consider whether you need to adjust your content marketing strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-seo-should-i-change-anything-for-google-knowledge-graph\">SEO: Should I Change Anything for Google Knowledge Graph?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The best response to Knowledge Graph is to make sure you communicate to Google key facts about your business, staff, authors, and products. This includes how they are connected to people, places, or things on the internet.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While basic facts may already be on your website, you can add more details by using <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/setting-web-page-schema-markup-in-your-content/\">schema markup</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Schema markup is code that Google reads to understand more about your site, business, people, and content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you add Schema markup to your site, you&#8217;re essentially adding &#8220;tags&#8221; for search engines to read. (And these â€œtagsâ€ are called â€œstructured data.â€)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding schema manually can be time-consuming.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thatâ€™s where a tool like the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) plugin comes in. It enables you to quickly add schema markup without knowing any code.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-add-schema-easily-with-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Add Schema Easily With All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you use WordPress, you can use the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) plugin to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-schema-markup-to-boost-your-seo/\">add schema</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It takes a few button clicks and you&#8217;ll fill out a form.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO has thousands of 5-star ratings on WordPress.org. And itâ€™s used by over 3 million bloggers and small businesses as well as large companies like Thomson Reuters FindLaw and Clorox.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"471\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-1024x471.png\" alt=\"aioseo-homepage\" class=\"wp-image-146993\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-1024x471.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-768x353.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-600x276.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage.png 1390w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>First, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">download and install the plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then follow these instructions:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/configuring-the-schema-settings-in-all-in-one-seo/#knowledge-graph-settings\">Add your website information for Knowledge Graph</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/local-business-seo-for-a-single-location/\">Add local SEO for a single-location business</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/local-business-seo-for-multiple-locations/\">Add local SEO for a multi-location business</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/displaying-your-social-media-profiles-in-knowledge-panel/\">Add your websiteâ€™s social media profiles</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Also consider adding an <strong>author bio</strong> for your writers. In that bio, link to other websites that the author is related to. And consider adding links to their social media profiles, too. These connections can help Google and other search engines understand more about your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-for-advanced-users-what-is-the-google-knowledge-graph-search-api\">For Advanced Users: What is the Google Knowledge Graph Search API?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Google Knowledge Graph Search API enables developers to access Knowledge Graph entities to create custom displays of related information on their websites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sample uses suggested by Google include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>&#8220;Getting a ranked list of the most notable entities that match certain criteria.&#8221;</li><li>&#8220;Predictively completing entities in a search box.&#8221;</li><li>&#8220;Annotating/organizing content using the Knowledge Graph entities.&#8221;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Google&#8217;s documentation says that they use standard Schema.org types, and the API is JSON-LD-compliant.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To use the API you&#8217;ll need to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Create an API key</li><li>Use Python, Java, JavaScript, or PHP</li><li>Understand JSON.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re using Python, you may find Google&#8217;s <a href=\"https://colab.research.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Colaboratory</a> helpful: it&#8217;s used widely for machine learning applications.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-did-google-create-the-first-knowledge-graph\">Did Google Create the First Knowledge Graph?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For millennia, humans have advanced their understanding of the world by classifying objects and concepts and exploring relationships between them. Those contributing to that understanding include philosophers, theologians, linguists, artists, scientists, novelists, and mathematicians.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Wikipedia, the term &#8220;knowledge graph&#8221; was coined in the 1970s and related projects began in the 1980s.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Readers interested in learning more about how the precursors and components of knowledge graphs evolved, including the semantic web and natural language processing (NLP), may enjoy <a href=\"https://knowledgegraph.today/paper.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">this research paper</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-whats-next\">What&#8217;s Next?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article gave you an easy-to-understand introduction to Google&#8217;s Knowledge Graph.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out our article on the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-product-review-plugins/\">best product review plugins</a> and how to use <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">WordPress FAQ blocks</a> to snatch market share from your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. Youâ€™ll find lots of helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-knowledge-graph/\">â€‹â€‹What is Google Knowledge Graph? A Super Simple Explanation</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://